umn list.\r\n     Explicitly by specifying NULL keyword in the VALUES clause","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":151,"Que":"What is the main difference between ‘BETWEEN’ and ‘IN’ condition operators?","Ans":"BETWEEN operator is used to display rows based on a range of values in a row whereas the IN condition operator is used to check for values contained in a specific set of values.\r\nExample of BETWEEN:\r\n     SELECT * FROM Students where ROLL_NO BETWEEN 10 AND 50;\r\nExample of IN:\r\n     SELECT * FROM students where ROLL_NO IN (8,15,25);","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":152,"Que":"Will following statement give Divide by Zero error?\r\n\r\nSELECT NULL/0","Ans":"No. It will execute and result will be NULL.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":153,"Que":"Will the following statements execute? if yes what will be output?\r\n\r\nSELECT NULL+1","Ans":"NULL","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":154,"Que":"Will the following statements execute? if yes what will be output?\r\n\r\nSELECT NULL+'1'","Ans":"NULL","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":155,"Que":"Will the following statements execute? if yes what will be output?\r\n\r\nSELECT AVG (NULL)","Ans":"Error\r\n\r\nOperand data type void type is invalid for avg operator.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":156,"Que":"What will be the output of given statement?\r\n\r\nSELECT MAX (NULL)","Ans":"Error\r\nOperand data type NULL is invalid for MAX operator.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":157,"Que":"What will be the output of given statement?\r\n\r\nSELECT SUM (NULL)","Ans":"Error\r\nCannot pass null type in SUM function.\r\nOperand data type NULL is invalid for avg operator.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":158,"Que":"How to increase the speed of a stored procedure?","Ans":"Insert SET NOCOUNT ON at the beginning of a stored procedure to suppress messages like