DisLikeCount":1,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":167,"Que":"Does View contain Data?","Ans":"No, Views are virtual structures.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":168,"Que":"What are the advantages of Views?","Ans":"Views restrict access to the data because the view can display selective columns from the table.\r\nViews can be used to make simple queries to retrieve the results of complicated queries. \r\nFor Example, views can be used to query information from multiple tables without the user knowing.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":169,"Que":"Explain the difference between Rename and Alias?","Ans":"Rename is a permanent name given to a table or column whereas Alias is a temporary name given to a table or column.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":1,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":170,"Que":"What is the Case function?","Ans":"Case facilitates if-then-else type of logic in SQL. It evaluates a list of conditions and returns one of the multiple possible result expressions.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":171,"Que":"What is Collation?","Ans":"Set of rules that define how data is stored, how case-sensitivity and Kana character can be treated etc.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":172,"Que":"What do you mean by query optimization?","Ans":"Query optimization is a process in which a database system compares different query strategies and select the query with the least cost.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":173,"Que":"What is a composite primary key?","Ans":"The primary key created on more than one column is called composite primary key.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":174,"Que":"What is an Index?","Ans":"An Index is a special structure associated with a table to speed up the performance of queries. The index can be created on one or more columns of a table.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":1},{"QueID":175,"Que":"What do you mean by ROWID?","Ans":"It’s an 18 character long pseudo column attached with each row of a table.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":176,"Que":"Which TCP/IP port does SQL Server run?","Ans":"By default SQL Server runs on port 1433.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":177,"Que":"What is Normalization?","Ans":"The process of table design to minimize the data redundancy is called normalization. We need to divide a database into two or more table and define the relationship between them.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":178,"Que":"Is it possible for a table to have more than one foreign key?","Ans":"Yes, a table can have many foreign keys but only one primary key.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":179,"Que":"What is the use of the NVL function?","Ans":"NVL function is used to convert the null value to its actual value.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":1},{"QueID":180,"Que":"What is SQL Injection?","Ans":"SQL Injection is a type of database attack technique where malicious SQL statements are inserted into an entry field of database in a way that once it is executed, the database is exposed to an attacker for the attack. This technique is usually used for attacking data-driven applications to have access to sensitive data and perform administrative tasks on databases.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":2},{"QueID":181,"Que":"Why using SELECT * in an SQL Query is a bad practice?","Ans":"1. Unnecessary I/O\r\n2. Increased network traffic\r\n3. More memory utilization","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":182,"Que":"When to use nvarchar data type in SQL Server?","Ans":"The NVARCHAR type stores up to 4000 characters with each character taking two bytes. NVARCHAR is well suited for storing extended character set data. Generally, If you're writing an application supporting multiple languages, then use NVARCHAR over VARCHAR.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":183,"Que":"Difference between UNION and UNION ALL in SQL?","Ans":"The main difference between UNION and UNION ALL is that UNION doesn't include duplicate record but UNION ALL does. \r\nAnother difference between them is that UNION ALL is faster than UNION but may look slow because it returns more data which takes more time to travel via the network.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0},{"QueID":184,"Que":"Describe the difference between clustered and non-clustered indexes in a database?","Ans":"Clustered index defined the order in which data is physically stored in the table. Since data can be sorted in only one way physically, there is only one clustered index per table and that's usually the primary key. You can have multiple non-clustered indexes to speed up your queries.","LikeCount":0,"DisLikeCount":0,"clapCount":0}]

